title: E & A Occupancy + Fire Sprinkler Information (City of San Antonio)

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Texas Public Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

I respectfully request an electronic, parcel-level extract containing current Group E (Educational) and Group A (Assembly) occupancies and associated fire-sprinkler information for all parcels within the jurisdiction: 

Please provide one CSV with the following columns (your native field names are fine):
- Parcel identifier (APN / PIN / BBL)
• Site address (street #, street, city, ZIP)
• Latitude & longitude
• Internal building / permit ID
• Year built
• Floor area (sq ft)
• Number of stories
• Current IBC occupancy code (E, A-1…A-5)

title: Georgia Public Records Act Request: Flock Safety audits and network sharing (Forsyth County Sheriff's Office)

communications.subject: Georgia Open Records Act Request: Georgia Public Records Act Request: Flock Safety audits and network sharing (Forsyth County Sheriff's Office)
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Georgia Open Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

Records related to the department’s Flock Safety system:
1. Organization Audit in Flock.
The report should include data logged from the period of December 1, 2024, to the date this request is processed. Per Flock's documentation, the Organization Audit is available within the Insights tab and is defined as searches done within the agency.

2. Network Audit in Flock.
The report should include data logged from the period of December 1, 2024, to the date this request is processed. Per Flock's documentation, the Network Audit is available within the Insights tab and is defined as searches of the organization’s Flock network by any agency in the Flock System.

3. A list of network share settings that include:
3a. Flock networks shared with me
3b. Flock networks shared with me Devices List (Please see https://cdn.muckrock.com/foia_files/2022/11/17/CPRA_REQUEST.pdf
https://cdn.muckrock.com/foia_files/2022/11/09/1938_001.pdf as examples of the lists from other jurisdictions.
3c. Networks that I’m sharing
3d. A list of agencies in the National Sharing/National Lookup network.

Please provide records in their original electronic, machine readable format. For example, please provide csv or spreadsheet files where applicable. Please do not redirect me to your transparency portal.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 3 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Paul Tepper

title: FBI File for Terry Gene Bollea, AKA "Hulk Hogan" or "the Hulkster," a noted performer

communications.subject: Freedom of Information Act Request: FBI File for Terry Gene Bollea, AKA "Hulk Hogan" or "the Hulkster," a noted performer
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

A copy of all segregable and releasable FBI records pertaining to Florida man or resident Terry Gene Bollea, AKA "Hulk Hogan" or "the Hulkster," (DOB: August 11, 1953; Deceased: July 24, 2025). Please note that Mr. Bollea's passing has been confirmed in public obituaries by major newspapers, including the New York Times and the Miami Herald:

https://www.nytimes.com/2025/07/24/sports/hulk-hogan-dead.html
https://www.miamiherald.com/entertainment/celebrities/article311320275.html

This search is to include each of the following record stores and interfaces: the Central Records System (CRS), the Automated Case Support system ("ACS") Investigative Case Management system ("ICM"), the Automated Case Support system ("ACS") Electronic Case File ("ECF"), and the Automated Case Support system ("ACS") Universal Index ("UNI").

I also request a search of "ELSUR", the database containing electronic surveillance information, for any and all records or activities related to Mr. Bollea — or his alter ego personae, such as "Hulk Hogan," or "Terry Boulder" of "The Boulder Brothers" — for any on-line account or address or associated service. In addition, please extend the search criteria across any external storage media, including I-Drives, S-Drives, or related technologies used during the course of Bureau investigations. Please include processing notes, even if this request is denied in part. Please identify individuals responsible for any aspect of FOIA processing in the processing notes, along with explanation of their involvement if not typically assigned FOIA responsibilities for the record systems above. Please include materials responsive to this request from the bureau's field offices, if possible, to reduce overlap with field office requests.

Note, also: I am a freelance reporter and would request that any relevant fees be waived. My past writing work has appeared in The Daily Mail, Mashable, The New York Times, New York magazine's Intelligencer blog, Scientific American, Slate.com, the New Republic, the New York Review of Books, Chemical Engineering magazine and elsewhere.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Matthew Phelan

title: Hulk Hogan

communications.subject: Freedom of Information Act Request: Hulk Hogan
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

Records mentioning, relating to, or generated as a result of investigation or inquiry into professional wrestler Terry Gene Bollea (August 11, 1953 – July 24, 2025), better known by his stage name, Hulk Hogan. His death is widely-known and widely reported; as such, privacy concerns under FOIA Exemptions 6 and 7 are voided, as are any concerns under the Privacy Act. For example, you may find his Fox News obituary at the following link: https://www.foxnews.com/sports/pro-wrestling-icon-hulk-hogan-dead

Please conduct a search of the Central Records System, including but not limited to the Electronic Surveillance (ELSUR) Indices, the Microphone Surveillance (MISUR) Indices, the Physical Surveillance (FISUR) Indices, and the Technical Surveillance (TESUR) Indices, for both main-file records and cross-reference records of both HQ and all field offices for all relevant names, agencies, organizations, companies and events including but not limited to those cited in the previous paragraphs and/or links as well as a cross-reference with the Southern Poverty Law Center to include any information provided by the SPLC. My request includes but is not limited to 137, 157, 176, 177, 183, 184, 188, and 214 files. If previously released records are available, then I request a rolling release consisting of those records while additional records are located and processed for release.

If any part of these documents are exempt from disclosure, please be sure to review and release all reasonably segregable nonexempt portions of responsive documents, as the FOIA requires.

I request that I be properly classified as a media requester. I am an assistant editor at Reason Magazine who has written numerous articles on topics of public interest, and I am requesting these documents in an editorial capacity. Please contact me if you have any questions about my media status.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.
